SIMPLE: insuperable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insuperable
<hw>In*su"per*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insuperabilis</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>insuperable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Superable</er>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of being
passed over or surmounted; insurmountable; <as>as, <ex>insuperable</ex>
difficulties</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And middle natures, how they long to join,⟦br⟧
Yet never pass the <qex>insuperable</qex> line?</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The difficulty is enhanced, or is . . .
<qex>insuperable</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Impassable; insurmountable;
unconquerable.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In*su"per*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>In*su"per*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insupportable</ent>⟦br⟧
